SIMPLE: fencing
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fencing
<hw>Fen"cing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The art
or practice of attack and defense with the sword, esp. with the
smallsword. See <er>Fence</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Disputing or debating in a manner resembling the art
of fencers.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The materials used for building fences.</def>
<mark>[U.S.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>The act of building a fence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>The aggregate of the fences put up for inclosure or
protection; <as>as, the <ex>fencing</ex> of a farm</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fen cricket</ent>⟦br⟧
